
msgid "Default value for max fiber slice"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The max fiber slice specifies the max fiber execution time without yield "
"before a warning is logged or an error is raised. It is set with the "
":ref:`fiber.set_max_slice() <fiber-set_max_slice>` function. The new "
"``compat`` option – ``fiber_slice_default`` – controls the default value of "
"the max fiber slice."
msgstr ""

msgid "Old and new behavior"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The old default value for the max fiber slice is infinity (no warnings or "
"errors). The new default value is ``{warn = 0.5, err = 1.0}``. To use the "
"new behavior, set ``fiber_slice_default`` to ``new`` as follows:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"compat = require('compat')\n"
"compat.fiber_slice_default = 'new'"
msgstr ""

